\b _______________\
               \
 PARAMETERS:   \
_______________
\b0 \
 \
VideoMax only takes 1 parameter, an Object, which is optional. This Object contains the specific (and optional) attributes to set in the VideoMax instance. The available attributes are:\
				\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\sa120\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\b \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}autoLoad (Boolean)
\b0  - If true, video will start loading upon instantiation. If false, video will not begin to load until play() is called. This value will be overwritten by a true value for autoPlay. (Default = true)
\b \
{\listtext	\'95	}autoPlay (Boolean)
\b0  - If true, will auto play the video. (Default = false)\
\ls2\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}autoRewind (Boolean)
\b0  - If true, will seek to the video start when the video is done. (Default = true)\
\ls2\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}autoSize (Boolean)
\b0  - If true, will automatically and proportionally scale the video inside the player. (Default = true)\
\ls2\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}buffer (Number)
\b0  - Number of seconds of buffer needed before the video plays. (Default = 3)\
\ls2\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}loop (Boolean)
\b0  - If true, video will auto-rewind (despite the autoRewind setting) and continue to loop playback. (Default = false)
\b \
{\listtext	\'95	}showControls (Boolean)
\b0  - If true, control bar is visible and active. (Default = true)\
{\listtext	\'95	}
\b showMiniStatus (Boolean)
\b0  - If true, mini status bar is visible when the control bar animates out. (Default = true)\
\ls2\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}source (String)
\b0  - The path to the video that you want to play. (Default = null)\
\ls2\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}tint (Array of uint)
\b0  - Array containing optional uint hex codes to tint (1) the control bar background elements, and (2) the control bar buttons and text elements. (Default = [0x000000, 0xffffff])\
\ls2\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}height (Number)
\b0  - The height of the VideoMax instance. (Default = 480)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\sa120\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\b \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}width  (Number)
\b0  - The width of the VideoMax instance. (Default = 640)\
{\listtext	\'95	}
\b playOverlay (Boolean)
\b0  - If true, shows large Play button overlay over video when not playing. (Default = false)\
\ls3\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}showFirstFrame (Boolean)
\b0  - If false, and autoPlay is false, hides video's first frame. (Default = true)\
\ls3\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}showLastFrame (Boolean)
\b0  - If false, and autoRewind is false, hides video's last frame. (Default = true)\
\ls3\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}showEndFrames (Boolean)
\b0  - If false, and autoPlay and autoRewind are false, hides video's first and last frames. Cancels out showFirstFrame and showLastFrame values, if set differently. (Default = true)\
\ls3\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}onComplete (Function)
\b0  - Function in parent file to be called when video completes. (Default = null)\
\ls3\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}onCompleteParams (Array)
\b0  - Array to pass in to onComplete function in parent file. (Default = null)\
\ls3\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}onStart (Function)
\b0  - Function in parent file to be called when video starts. (Default = null)\
\ls3\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}onStartParams (Array)
\b0  - Array to pass in to onStart function in parent file. (Default = null)\
{\listtext	\'95	}
\b enableFullScreen (Boolean)
\b0  - If set to true, will include 'full screen' button in control bar, and add stage resize listeners. Note that if this is set to 'true', the 'allowFullScreen' parameter in your HTML embed code MUST be set to 'true' to properly work. Also, a very important note for full screen is that if it's set to 'true', the VideoMax object should be the ONLY object on your stage, as it will auto-resize to the dimensions of the stage.\
