\
 PUBLIC METHODS:\
_________________
\b0 \
\
With VideoMax, you can call a number of public methods from the parent file. These methods are outlined below.\
	\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\sa120\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\ls4\ilvl0
\b \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}play()
\b0  - Resets the buffer, and reloads the video from the source location. Use when updating buffer length, or changing the source location for your video.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}resume()
\b0  - Resumes playback from the current playhead location. Use when the video has been paused or stopped, as it will NOT completely reload the video like the play() method does. \
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}pause()
\b0  - Pauses playback.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}stop()
\b0  - Stops playback and returns the playhead to the beginning of the video. Since there is no built-in stop button in the Control Bar, use this method for stopping and resetting the video to the start.\
{\listtext	\'95	}
\b reset()
\b0  - Stops playback, resets source to null, and hides video.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}mute(Boolean)
\b0  - Mutes/Unmutes sound, based on the passed Boolean value into the function. A 'true' value mutes sound. A 'false' value unmutes sound.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}getElapsed()
\b0  - Returns the elapsed time as a Number.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}getDuration()
\b0  - Returns the duration of the video as a Number.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}setSize(width, height)
\b0  - Sets video width and height, which are passed in as parameters. Passed width and height need to be typed as Numbers. (Default = 640, 480)\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}setAutoLoad(Boolean) - 
\b0 If true, video will start loading upon instantiation. If false, video will not begin to load until play() is called. This value will be overwritten by a true value for autoPlay. (Default = true)
\b \
{\listtext	\'95	}setAutoPlay(Boolean)
\b0  - If true, sets video to auto play. (Default = false)\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}setAutoRewind(Boolean)
\b0  - If true, video seeks to the start when the video is done. (Default = true)\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}setAutoSize(Boolean)
\b0  - If true, video will automatically and proportionally scale the video inside the player. (Default = true)\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}setLoop(Boolean)
\b0  - If true, video will auto-rewind (despite the autoRewind setting) and continue to loop playback. (Default = false)\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}setTint(cbHex,btnHex)
\b0  - Sets Control Bar tint. Passed parameters are uint values for (1) background elements, and (2) button and text elements. (Default = 0x000000, 0xffffff)\
{\listtext	\'95	}
\b setVolume(Number)
\b0  - Sets volume level. A setting of 0 is mute, and 1 is 100%. This value can be more than 1, though audio quality may suffer. (Default = 1)\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}setBuffer(Number)
\b0  - Sets the number of seconds of buffer needed before the video plays. (Default = 3)\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}showVideo(Boolean)
\b0  - Shows/Hides video inside of player. (Default = true)\
\ls4\ilvl0
\b {\listtext	\'95	}showControlBar(Boolean)
\b0  - Shows/Hides control bar inside of player. (Default = true)\
{\listtext	\'95	}
\b showMiniStatusBar(Boolean)
\b0  - Shows/Hides mini status bar that shows when control bar is not visible. (Default = true)\
